00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.160
In the middle of your course homepage, you'll find your list of assignments.

1
00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:13.920
This allows you to easily view the assignment type, as well as the start and due dates.

2
00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:18.160
Connect offers a variety of assignment types, allowing your instructor to set specific policies

3
00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:24.860
for each, such as number of attempts, time limits, late submission allowances, and feedback.

4
00:00:24.860 --> 00:00:29.280
To view these assignment details, click on the arrow at the end of the assignment line.

5
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:33.620
important to carefully review the assignment details before starting the assignment.

6
00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:38.200
Some assignments, for example, only allow a limited number of attempts or have a time limit,

7
00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:40.460
so be careful before jumping in.

8
00:00:40.460 --> 00:00:44.540
When you are truly ready to begin the assignment, click on begin.

9
00:00:44.540 --> 00:00:49.400
In some cases, your instructor allows the use of resources for assignment completion.

10
00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:54.160
These prompts will be located on the left side of the page and below the question.

11
00:00:54.160 --> 00:01:10.225
The references icon provides information about the question type your question and then use the navigation buttons to move on to the other questions Remember your assignment may be timed in which case the clock will still run even if you choose to save and exit the assignment

12
00:01:10.225 --> 00:01:16.225
If it is not timed, you may click save and exit at any time to save your work and return to it later.

13
00:01:16.225 --> 00:01:20.225
When you've completed the assignment, click the submit button,

14
00:01:20.225 --> 00:01:26.225
followed by the exit button to return to the main menu.

15
00:01:26.225 --> 00:01:31.104
In addition to homework, quizzes, and exams, Connect offers a unique assignment called SmartBook.

16
00:01:31.845 --> 00:01:40.285
SmartBook provides personalized learning to you as an individual, continually adapting to pinpoint where you need help to ensure that you master the course content.

17
00:01:41.384 --> 00:01:45.405
SmartBook takes the guesswork out of what to study and helps you better prepare for class.

18
00:01:45.905 --> 00:01:52.005
And with the Read Anywhere mobile app, you can now read and complete SmartBook 2.0 assignments, both online and offline.

19
00:01:53.285 --> 00:01:56.205
If your instructor has assigned smart book, you can learn more in a search.

20
00:01:56.225 --> 00:01:58.225
separate smart book tutorial.